6.Enumerate The Process To Check Whether A Given Input Is Numeric , Integer ,
Double, Complex in R.
Program:
num&lt;-6
integer1&lt;-4.8
complex1&lt;-2+3i
double1&lt;-&quot;5&quot;
print(is.numeric(num))
print(is.integer(integer1))
print(is.complex(complex1))
print(is.double(double1))

Output:

7. Illustration of Vector Arithmetic.
Program:
a&lt;-c(1, 9, 5, 7)
b&lt;-c(1, 2, 4, 8)
x=4*a
print(&quot;4*a=&quot;)
print(x)
print(&quot;a+b=&quot;)
ad=a+b
print(ad)
subb=a-b
print(&quot;a-b=&quot;)
print(subb)
multi=a*b
print(&quot;a*b=&quot;)
print(multi)
divi=a/b
print(&quot;a/b=&quot;)
print(divi)
Output:

8. Write an R Program to Take Input From User.
Input name as “Jack” and age as 17.
The program should display the output as
“Hai , Jack next year you will be 18 years old”
Program:
name&lt;-&quot;Jack&quot;
age&lt;-18
x=sprintf(&quot;Hai, %s next year you will be %d years old&quot;,name,age)
